id: pm-zcjy
title: "contracts-snapshot gate is environment-dependent: fixture baked in installed-extension contracts, failing CI on extension version drift or absence"
description: "scripts/contracts-snapshot.mjs ran pm contracts --full against the repo tracker with active extensions, so the checked-in fixture depended on which pm-changelog version happened to be vendored — the 2026.7.10 upstream refresh and the vendored-dist untracking each broke the static gate on main."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: ci,contracts,determinism,extensions
created_at: "2026-07-10T11:59:03.050Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-10T11:59:16.849Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-10T11:59:03.050Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: "Snapshot generation runs pm --no-extensions contracts --full so the fixture captures only baseline CLI/SDK contracts; check passes identically with the extension present, absent, or at any upstream version; fixture regenerated (extension-contributed entries removed); main CI green"
risk: low
confidence: high
severity: high
environment: "CI Gates (static) on main, commits bac1c4c7 + 21a7d884"
repro_steps: "pnpm changelog:pm:install upgrading the vendored pm-changelog (or removing it) then node scripts/contracts-snapshot.mjs --check -> stale at line 1324 (upgrade) or line 34 (absent)"
resolution: Snapshot generation switched to pm --no-extensions contracts --full; fixture regenerated baseline-only
expected_result: Static gate deterministic regardless of installed extension state or upstream version
actual_result: check passes byte-identically with pm-changelog present and absent; 32 files / 511 script+integration tests green
